  note         = {Mechanistic review linking venous stasis to glymphatic impairment. Venous congestion increases intracranial venous pressure → reduced perivascular CSF flow → impaired glymphatic clearance. Waste accumulation (amyloid-beta, tau, cytokines) affects hypothalamic arousal systems (orexin, locus coeruleus). Reviews glymphatic dysfunction evidence in ME/CFS (reduced DTI-ALPS scores in 65\% of patients). Proposes venous decompression may improve glymphatic function. Orexin neuron vulnerability aligns with ME/CFS orexin deficiency hypothesis. Theoretical framework; requires clinical validation.}
}

